title: SOCE FILING HANGGANG HUNYO 13 LANG
content:
INIHAYAG NG COMMISSION ON ELECTIONS NA HANGGANG SA HUNYO TRESE NA LANG PUWEDENG MAGHAIN NG STATEMENT OF CONTRIBUTIONS AND EXPENDITURES O SOCE ANG LAHAT NG MGA KUMANDIDATO SA ISINAGAWANG BARANGAY AT SANGGUNIANG KABATAAN ELECTIONS.

NILINAW DIN NI COMELEC SPOKESPERSON JAMES JIMENEZ NA MAGING ANG MGA NADISKUWALIPIKA AY KAILANGAN DIN MAGSUMITE NG NASABING SOCE.

BATAY SA SECTION 14 NG R.A. 7166 KAILANGAN ANG PAGHAHAIN NG SOCE DAHIL HINDI MAAARING MAGLINGKOD ANG NAHALAL HANGGANG HINDI NAKAKASUMITE NITO.

author: admin
title: 6 KATAO ARESTADO KABILANG ANG ISANG HIGH VALUE TARGET MATAPOS ANG ISINAGAWANG BUY BUST OPERATION SA ISANG INN SA DARAGA, ALBAY; AABOT SA DALAWANG MILYONG HALAGA NG SHABU NAREKOBER
content:
Nasampahan na ng kasong paglabag sa Republic Act 9165 o Comprehensive Dangerous Drugs Act of 2002 ang mga suspect na naaresto sa isinagawang operasyon ng pinag-isang pwersa ng Philippine Drug Enforcement Agency at ng Philippine National Police nitong nakalipas na linggo.

Matatandaan na naaresto ang anim na katao kabilang na ang itinuturing na High Value Target ng PDEA matapos ang isinagawang drug buy-bust operation sa Neuhauz inn sa Purok 7, Brgy. Bagtang, Maroroy, Daraga, Albay.

Naikasa ang nasabing operasyon sa pakikipagtulungan ng PDEA Sorsogon, Provincial Office, PDEA Regional Special Enforcement, Daraga Municipal Police Station at iba pang mga law enforcement agencies.

Sa room 61 ng naturang inn, dakung alas dose diyes ng madaling araw, naaresto sina Marlon Fernandez alyas Bok Fernandez ng Brgy. Iraya, Guinobatan, Lorraine Santiago ng Antipolo City at Elmer Cunthada ng Sinuha Village, Brgy. Mambugan, Antipolo City.

Si Fernandez ay itinuturing High Value Target at isa sa mga malalaking supplier ng droga sa Camarines Sur at Sorsogon.

Nakumpiska mula sa mga suspek ang aabot sa dalawang daan limampung gramo ng shabu na nagkakahalaga ng 1.5 million pesos at mga drug paraphernalia.

Sa room 49 naman sa kaparehong establisyimento sa oras na ala una ng madaling araw, nadakip naman si Mark Rapisura ng Travesia, Guinobatan, Jose Tabuena ng First Park Subdivision, Sagpon, Daraga, albay at Jonel Dela Druz ng Dunao, Ligao City.

Ayon sa mga operatiba, ang mga ito ay supplier ng mga iligal na droga sa mga eskwelahan at mga estudyante partikular na sa probinsya ng Albay.

Nasamsam mula sa mga suspek ang aabot sa limampung gramo ng shabu na nagkakahalaga ng tatlong daang libong piso at mga drug paraphernalia.

author: ADMIN
title: 3 BIKOLANO NANGUNA SA MIDWIFERY LICENSURE EXAM NITONG NAKALIPAS NA NOBYEMBRE
content:
Tatlong Bikolano ang nanguna mula sa 3,360 na sumailalim sa Midwife Licensure Exam na ginanap noong nakaraang Nobyembre, isa ang nanguna mula sa Masbate Colleges, isa sa Catanduanes State University at isa sa Bicol University Tabaco Campus, batay yan sa ipinalabas ng Professional Regulation Commission (PRC) kahapon, Nobyembre 8.

Mula sa Masbate Colleges, pumangalawa si Joel Cadag Almoguerra sa kanyang nakuhang 88.65% na marka, pangalawa rin si Connie Jane Manlangit Convicto na may 88.65% na marka ng Catanduanes State University at pangwalo naman si Stephen Kyle Dela Cruz Sierra sa kanyang markang 87.45% ng Bicol University Tabaco Campus.

 

Kabuuang 1,444 ang pumasa mula sa 3,360 na sumailalim sa naturag pagsusulit batay sa ibinigay na datos ng Board of Midwifery mula sa iba ibang testing centers sa buong bansa.

author: admin
title: OPLAN GREYHOUND IKINASA NG PNP SA DAET MUNICIPAL POLICE STATION
content:
Ikinasa ng Daet PNP ang Oplan Greyhound sa selda ng Daet Municipal Police station Nagsagawa ng Oplan Greyhound ang Daet PNP sa mismong mga selda ng Daet Municipal Police Station nitong Martes na pinangunahan ni Police Superintendent Juancho Ibis, hepe ng Daet PNP

Ayon kay Ibis, isinagawa nila ang inspeksyon dahil madaming inmates sa naturang piitan ang sangkot sa illegal na droga at nais nitong doblehin ang pagbabantay sa mga ito.

Napag-alaman din kasi na nagkakaroon ng mga bagay na ipinagbabawal sa loob ng selda.

Sa naturang inspeksyon, nakakuha sila ng dalawang cellphone, apat na lighter, tatlong piraso ng blade ang mga kaha ng sigarilyo.

Nakakuha din sila umano ng pinaniniwalaang pharaphernalia na posibleng ginagamit ng mga inmates.

Matapos ang inspeksyon ay nagsagawa din ng pagbabago ng schedule ng pagdalawa ng mga kamag-anak ng mga preso.

author: admin
title: MULTI-YEAR FLOOD CONTROL PROJECT SA LALAWIGAN NG CAMARINES NORTE INIHAHANDA NA NG DPWH
content:
Inihahanda na ng Department of Public Works and Highways ang long time program upang tugunan ang problema sa baha sa lalawigan ng Camarines Norte.

Ayon kay District Engineer Ricardo gutierez, magsisimula ang programa para sa flood control sa susunod ng taon at kailangan multi-year programming dahil malalaki umano ang kailugan sa naturang lalawigan.

Ibig sabihin, simula 2019 hangang 2022 ay aayusin ng DPWH ang pagkakasunud-sunod ng paglalaanan ng pondo para sa flood control structure.

Sa kabilang daku, patuloy ang isinasagawang declogging activites ng ahensya sa mga kanal partikular na sa bayan ng Daet.

Kaugnay nito, problema nila umano ang outlet na dadaanan ng tubig lalo na ngayon panahon ng tag-ulan at sa ngayon ay nagpapahanap sila ng magsasagawa ng master plan sa naturang bayan.

author: admin
title: EBMC SA LALAWIGAN NG CATANDUANES NAGBUKAS NG BAGONG OUTSOURCED PHARMACY
content:
Nagbukas ang Eastern Bicol Medical Center (EBMC) sa pakikipagtulungan ng Planet Drugstore ng bagong outsourced pharmacy sa lalawigan ng Catanduanes para sa mas abot kayang presyo at magandang kalidad ng gamot para sa mga pasyente.

Ayon kay EBMC OIC Dr. Ma. Consuelo Barceta, ito ay paraan nila upang matugunan ang kakulangan sa suplay ng mga gamot na labis na nakaaapekto sa serbisyong medikal sa mga pasyente lalung-lalo na sa mga kapus-palad na mamamayan.

Ayon naman kay Erwin Jayson Zshornack, owner at General Manager ng Planet Durgstore, sila umano ang mamamahala sa pharmacy at imbentaryo ng mga gamot.

Sinigurado din ni Zshornack na magbibigay sila ng libreng pharmacy staff upang matulungan ang ospital ng walang gastos ng pamahalaan.

Nagpasalamat din si Zshornack sa probinsya ng Catanduanes sa ibinigay na pagkakataon na makatulong at makapagbigay ng serbisyo sa mga tao.

Samantala, pinuri naman ni Governor Joseph Cua ang Board of Trustees (BoT) dahil sa pagtugon sa isyu na kinkaharap ng EBMC.

Masaya ding ibinalita ni Cua na magkakaroon ng karagadagang pasilidad at ikipahe ang ospital gayan ng CT Scan, Hemodialysis Machines, Respiratory Unit TB-DOTS Facility, Drug Testing Center, radiology Room at iba pa.

author: admin
title: Comment: Putin is afraid of one thing. Make him think it could happen.
content:
Editor’s note: The opinions in this article are the author’s, as published by our content partner, and do not necessarily represent the views of MSN or Microsoft.

Facebook revealed on July 31 that it had discovered a 17-month-long influence campaign to sow political divisiveness on its network, an effort that bore the hallmarks of the Kremlin-connected Internet Research Agency. 

Two days later at the White House, the nation’s top national security officials said Russia is conducting a pervasive campaign to weaken our democracy and influence this year’s midterm elections. 

Taken together, these announcements leave no doubt that Russian President Vladi­mir Putin’s political assault on the United States continues unabated.

The most important question the Trump administration and Congress should be asking is: How can we make Putin stop? Finding the answer is essential because what Washington has done so far — some improvements in defending against these attacks, along with a mixture of targeted sanctions against Russia, the indictment of Russian officials and organisations, as well as the expulsion of Russian intelligence officers from the United States — has not worked.

Stopping Putin is vital, not just as a matter of protecting American democracy from Russian interference but also because we must signal a stronger deterrence to other adversaries, such as China, Iran and North Korea. Potential aggressors must be shown they will pay a price if they attack. 

With better resources than Russia for trying to undermine our democracy, China, in particular, needs to know that the United States would respond by imposing a heavy cost.

The U.S. answer to Russia, so far, has been ineffective because Washington has targeted only the entities and individuals actually involved in the Russian information operations. 

Since the 2016 election, the United States, at various times, has imposed sanctions on at least 10 Russian organisations, some more than once, and at least 23 specific individuals. 

Because the sanctions’ targeting has had little impact on the Russian economy overall, the political effect on Putin has been minor.

Here is what the United States needs to do. In terms of self-defence, it must secure the nation’s elections system, especially the software that holds data on registered voters. 

Every vote should be tallied on a backup paper ballot that could be used to verify election results, if necessary. New rules and better enforcement are needed to keep foreign money out of U.S. elections. 

The federal government should work with individual campaigns to fortify the security of the technology and networks they use. 

Finally, better coordination across the government is needed to protect U.S. elections, which would probably best be achieved by creating a Hybrid Threats Center similar to the National Counterterrorism Center.

There are several bills in Congress, all with support on both sides of the aisle, that would institute most of these changes and pay for them, but the legislation is frozen by the partisanship this issue stirs.

As for imposing costs on those who attack the United States: Fully implement sanctions already on the books. 

That is still not happening. But then move beyond targeted sanctions to broad-based sanctions that are designed to hurt the Russian economy — just as the Obama administration’s sanctions against Iran were designed to do, as are the Trump administration’s. 

Make it clear to Putin that we would drop the sanctions when he stopped interfering in the democratic institutions of the United States and its allies, some of which are also under siege.

What would such sanctions look like? A Senate bill introduced on Aug. 2, again with sponsors from both parties, is a good start: Prohibit any transaction related to Russian energy projects and bar the purchase of new Russian sovereign debt. Washington should encourage its allies to join in these efforts.

Putin is afraid of one thing. He is afraid that one day the Russian middle class will finally rebel against his regime and rush into the streets demanding change. 

It happened in Tunis, Cairo and other Middle Eastern and North African cities between 2010 and 2012, and it happened most alarmingly, from Putin’s perspective, four years ago in Kiev when Ukrainians threw out a government beholden to Moscow. 

Sanctions that bite at the heart of the Russian economy — sanctions that increase the risk that Russia’s middle class will become restive — will get Putin’s attention.

The leaders that the United States has chosen, and the security experts they have appointed and confirmed, are aware of the threat. 

A failure to defend the nation as well as possible, and failure to impose severe costs on those attacking our democracy, would be seen by history as a major abdication of responsibility. 

The statements from intelligence officials at the White House last week were an excellent first step. More steps, and stronger ones are urgently needed.

author: admin
title: Pacquiao must do research on Bible passage about death penalty, CBCP exec says
content:
An official of the Catholic Bishops Conference of the Philippines (CBCP) on Wednesday said Senator Manny Pacquiao should conduct a comprehensive research about Bible teachings first before making interpretations of its passages.

"Kasi ang Bible o kahit anong mga salita, meron 'yang context. Siguro he should ask his staff to do some research. Mare-research naman ang kahulugan niyan at a particular time kasi cinite niya 'yung sa Romans, Hebrews... Hindi nga gospel 'yung kaniyang cinite," Rodolfo Diamante, executive secretary of the CBCP Commission on Prison Pastoral Care, told Balitanghali.

"Maganda naman kasi he's a public figure, ina-idolize din ng marami... 'Pag nagsalita siya, pinaniniwalaan. Pero anong kahulugan ng salita? 'Yun ang pinakamahalaga," Diamante said.

"Basta 'pag sinabi mo na iyan ay nakasulat sa Bibliya and all those things, hindi naman gano'n. When the Pope pronounce something and improve on the teachings of the Church, it is a result of a very in-depth study, not only of himself but a group of scripture scholars. So meron tayo no'n," he added.

As he pushes for the reinstatement of death penalty in the country, Pacquiao recently cited Romans 13:1-7 as proof that God gave people the authority to "impose death penalty [on] those who commit heinous crimes."

"Kung mabasa mo sa Bible, do not kill, individually. Pero pagdating sa government, the government has authority to impose death penalty. Basahin niyo 'yung Romans 13," the lawmaker said.

Diamante deemed the lawmaker's understanding of the passage as "misleading" for the public.

He said the CBCP has provided enough materials on death penalty which Pacquiao may check.

"Sa parte namin, we have given almost all the materials that are needed, in fact, kung titingnan lang ni Senator Pacquiao 'yung binigay sa kaniya, 'yung materials ng CBCP, 'yung pastoral statement, meron kaming source book on the issue of death penalty talking about the anthropological, sociological aspect, spiritual aspect," Diamante said.

"If they will only really listen and open their mind into it, I'm very sure na they will agree na hindi talaga dapat i-reimpose ang death penalty," he added.

The Vatican recently declared the death penalty as inadmissible "in the light of the Gospel," but Pacquiao is pushing to have the proposed death penalty bill approved in the Senate before the year ends.

author: admin
title: Duterte to meet PDP-Laban officials, faction
content:
President Rodrigo Duterte is set to meet Thursday afternoon the officials of Partido Demokratiko Pilipino-Lakas ng Bayan and the group claiming to be the new officers of the political party.

Senator Aquilino Pimentel III, PDP-Laban president, said the meeting will take place at a hotel in Manila.

Aside from Pimentel, Duterte, PDP-Laban chairman, will also be meeting lawyer Rogelio Garcia, who was supposedly elected as new party president when some officials of the regional councils held a national assembly in July. 

As early as July 20, Pimentel's group has already issued a “notice to the public” to warn the people against individuals who identify themselves as officers of the political party.

The party said it has come to its attention that some individuals have called for a national assembly on July 27 at the Amoranto Amphitheater in Quezon City.

The party said such event and the faction's other activities are not officially sanctioned.

Pimentel said those who participated in the national assembly would face sanction, including expulsion.

The senator maintained that the officers of the PDP-Laban are as follows: Duterte as chairman; vice chairman, Energy Secretary Alfonso Cusi; him as president; and secretary general, former Speaker Pantaleon Alvarez
